old Map 5 was a non-sj filtered table read
old Map 7 was an sj filtered scan

the old Map 5 and old Map 7 is now merged into the new Map 5 vertex - which is not SJ filtered because we already scan the table.
I also think that it might be beneficial to retain the SJ filter condition in cases like this and start prefiltering at this point ; I've opened HIVE-24376 to do that a few weeks ago - is that what you meaned?
